  <num>25-784</num>
  <heading>Sale or distribution of beverages by minor prohibited.</heading>
  <para>
    <num>(a)</num>
    <text>Except as provided in subsection (b) of this section, a licensee shall not allow any person under 21 years of age to sell, give, furnish, or distribute an alcoholic beverage.</text>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(b)</num>
    <text>A licensee may allow an employee who is 18 years of age or older to sell, serve, or deliver an alcoholic beverage on the licensed premises; provided, that no employee under 21 years of age shall serve as a bartender.</text>
  </para>
